            <p class="text-justify">Aegean Airlines is the largest Greek airline in Greece headquartered in Kifisia, a suburb of Athens.The airline operates scheduled and charter services from Athens and Thessaloniki to other major Greek destinations as well as to a number of European and Middle Eastern destinations.</p>
            <p class="text-justify">The airline connects popular holiday destinations in Greece to Italy, France, the United Kingdom, Poland, Israel, Romania, Russia, Sweden, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, Norway, Slovenia, Austria, Germany, Hungary, Ukraine, and other countries. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">If you are planning for a holiday to one of the destinations mentioned, you may <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/aegean-airlines-flights.aspx">book flight tickets with Aegean airlines</a>. The airline has a hassle-free flight booking and flight cancellation policy. Let’s have a look at the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/aegean-airlines-cancellation-policy.aspx">cancellation policy of Aegean airlines</a>. </p>
            <h2>Cancellation</h2>
            <p class="text-justify">If you cancel your flight reservation within 24 hours of booking when the flight’s scheduled departure must be 7 days or more; you don’t need to pay any cancellation fee. If you cancel the flight after 24 hours of booking, you can pay 20 ERU up to 30 minutes of departure of the flight. From then on, the cancellation fee depends on the type of fare, the destination, and significantly on the time of cancellation of the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">flight tickets</a> somewhere between 100 USD to 500 USD. </p>
            <h3>Refund</h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If you have successfully canceled the flight reservation within 24 hours of booking, you are eligible to receive a 100% refund. If you have canceled the flight reservation near the flight departure time, the refund would be less as compared to cancellations made within 24 hours. You may also contact your kiosk to help you with refund-related issues on your behalf. </p>
            <h4>frequently asked questions</h4>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with Aegean Airlines? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can call the Aegean Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. You may also contact your kiosk to help you through the cancellation process. Apart from this, you may also visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">When can I make the request for the refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can make a request for a refund by filling out a refund request form on Aegean Airlines’ official website. The refund will reflect within 7 to 20 business days from the cancellation. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">If your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How to check if my flight is refundable? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number and Aegean Airlines’ website will display refund eligibility and information. </p>


